SiteOne Landscape Supply Inc (NYSE:SITE) Stake Increased by Bank of New York Mellon Corp

					Posted by Kim Johansen on Jul 25th, 2017 // No Comments 




Bank of New York Mellon Corp raised its stake in  SiteOne Landscape Supply Inc (NYSE:SITE) by 154.2% during the first quarter, according to its most recent disclosure with the Securities and Exchange Commission. The firm owned 192,159 shares of the industrial products company’s stock after buying an additional 116,564 shares during the period. Bank of New York Mellon Corp owned 0.49% of SiteOne Landscape Supply worth $9,303,000 at the end of the most recent quarter. 
A number of other large investors have also added to or reduced their stakes in SITE. Conestoga Capital Advisors LLC increased its stake in  SiteOne Landscape Supply by 3.5% in the first quarter. Conestoga Capital Advisors LLC now owns 792,434 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $38,362,000 after buying an additional 26,749 shares during the last quarter.  Bank of Montreal Can purchased a new stake in  SiteOne Landscape Supply during the first quarter worth about $1,589,000.  Teachers Advisors LLC increased its stake in  SiteOne Landscape Supply by 3.9% in the fourth quarter. Teachers Advisors LLC now owns 18,882 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $656,000 after buying an additional 711 shares in the last quarter.  UBS Asset Management Americas Inc. purchased a new stake in  SiteOne Landscape Supply during the fourth quarter worth about $219,000.  Finally, Teachers Retirement System of The State of Kentucky increased its stake in  SiteOne Landscape Supply by 23.3% in the fourth quarter. Teachers Retirement System of The State of Kentucky now owns 23,902 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $830,000 after buying an additional 4,514 shares in the last quarter. Institutional investors own  87.83% of the company’s stock. 


 Get SiteOne Landscape Supply Inc alerts:



SiteOne Landscape Supply Inc (NYSE:SITE) traded down 1.07% on Tuesday, hitting $52.88. The stock had a trading volume of 409,412 shares. The stock’s market cap is $2.10 billion. SiteOne Landscape Supply Inc has a 12 month low of $26.60 and a 12 month high of $53.87. The company’s 50 day moving average is $51.83 and its 200-day moving average is $45.96. 




SiteOne Landscape Supply (NYSE:SITE) last posted its earnings results on Wednesday, May 10th. The industrial products company reported ($0.26) EPS for the quarter, topping the consensus estimate of ($0.27) by $0.01. The firm had revenue of $335 million for the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $335.53 million. SiteOne Landscape Supply had a negative return on equity of 29.18% and a negative net margin of 3.13%. SiteOne Landscape Supply’s revenue for the quarter was up 2.0% compared to the same quarter last year. During the same period last year, the company earned ($0.85) earnings per share.  Analysts forecast that  SiteOne Landscape Supply Inc will post $1.40 EPS for the current year. 
TRADEMARK VIOLATION NOTICE: “SiteOne Landscape Supply Inc (NYSE:SITE) Stake Increased by Bank of New York Mellon Corp” was first  published by Markets Daily and is the property of of Markets Daily. If you are viewing this piece of content on another website, it was illegally stolen and reposted in violation of international copyright & trademark laws. The legal version of this piece of content can be accessed at https://www.themarketsdaily.com/2017/07/25/siteone-landscape-supply-inc-site-position-boosted-by-bank-of-new-york-mellon-corp-updated-updated.html. 
A number of equities research analysts have issued reports on SITE shares. Royal Bank Of Canada  restated a “buy” rating and set a $52.00 price target on shares of SiteOne Landscape Supply in a research note on Monday, May 8th. Johnson Rice started coverage on SiteOne Landscape Supply in a research note on Monday, May 8th. They set an “accumulate” rating for the company. Finally, Zacks Investment Research upgraded SiteOne Landscape Supply from a “hold” rating to a “buy” rating and set a $53.00 price target for the company in a research note on Wednesday, April 19th. Four analysts have rated the stock with a hold rating and one  has issued  a buy rating to the company’s stock. SiteOne Landscape Supply  has an average rating of “Hold” and a consensus target price of $49.00.
In other news, CEO Doug Black bought 6,200 shares of the firm’s stock in a transaction dated Thursday, May 25th. The shares were acquired at an average price of $50.76 per share, for a total transaction of $314,712.00. Following the completion of the transaction, the chief executive officer now directly owns 400,743 shares in the company, valued at approximately $20,341,714.68. The acquisition was disclosed in a filing with the SEC, which is available through the SEC website. Also, major shareholder & Co Deere sold 3,998,550 shares of SiteOne Landscape Supply stock in a transaction that occurred on Monday, May 1st. The stock was sold at an average price of $46.08, for a total value of $184,253,184.00. The disclosure for this sale can be found here. 4.00% of the stock is owned by company insiders. 
About SiteOne Landscape Supply
SiteOne Landscape Supply, Inc is a national wholesale distributor of landscape supplies in the United States and Canada. The Company is a supplier of irrigation, landscape lighting, hardscapes, lawn care supplies, nursery stock, and landscape accessories to green industry professionals. As of October 2, 2016, the Company had over 450 stores.







